I coordinate corporate transportation for executives at a Denver tech company, and after eight years of booking private car service from Denver airport to downtown, I've learned that the biggest delay isn't traffic or distance. It's the 15-minute gap between when your driver arrives at the airport and when you actually get in the car.

Most people think private car service means your driver pulls up wherever you are and off you go. Denver International Airport's ground transportation system doesn't work that way, and this creates timing problems that catch business travelers off guard every single time.

